          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "What does AEO stand for in marketing?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "AEO stands for Answer Engine Optimization, which is the process of optimizing web content to be selected and cited as authoritative answers by AI-powered search and answer engines. [geo-arxiv]"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "How is AEO different from SEO?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "AEO focuses on optimizing for inclusion in AI-driven answer engines like ChatGPT and Google Gemini, while SEO targets traditional search rankings. AEO requires concise answers, structured data, and authority signals for citation in AI responses. [openai-docs, google-search-central]"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "What are the main factors that influence AEO ranking?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Main AEO ranking factors include content quality, the presence of structured data (like schema.org markup), E-E-A-T signals, clear answers, authoritative sources, and verifiable citations. [openai-docs, google-search-central]"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Which engines should brands optimize for with AEO?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Key platforms include ChatGPT (OpenAI), Google Gemini, Claude, and Perplexity AI. These engines rely on content structure, authority, and explicit answers for citation in results. [openai-docs, google-search-central]"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Is AEO relevant for all industries?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "AEO is relevant for any industry where users seek clear, authoritative answers via AI-driven search engines and chatbots. This includes B2B, SaaS, healthcare, finance, and more. [gartner-ai-search]"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "How do you measure AEO performance?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "AEO performance is measured by tracking share-of-voice across AI answer engines, monitoring how often your content is cited, and analyzing prompt-specific response rates—platforms like AnswerMonk specialize in these metrics. [geo-arxiv]"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "What is GEO and how does it relate to AEO?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "GEO (Generative Engine Optimization) is a broader paradigm that includes AEO but also targets model prompt testing, citation tactics, and structured statistics for generative engine responses. [geo-arxiv]"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Will AEO replace SEO?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "AEO will not fully replace SEO but is becoming critical as a supplementary discipline, given that up to 25% of search traffic may move to answer engines by 2026. [gartner-ai-search]"
          }
        }
